refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
public voidAtomicInteger::set intvalue
This method will set the value of the atomic integer. Internally, the mutex lock of the atomic integer will be acquired, and so there is no need to manually acquire it (unless this operation needs to be grouped with other operations on the same atomic integer - see the example in AtomicInteger::lock for a demonstration of this).

&reftitle.parameters;


  value



    The value to set the atomic integer to.

  &reftitle.examples;



    Setting an atomic integer's value


<?php

use pht\AtomicInteger;

$atomicInteger = new AtomicInteger();

$atomicInteger->set(20);

var_dump($atomicInteger->get());


    &example.outputs;


int(20)
